see #20 

All mutability for IronOxide has been moved inside the SDK.

Here's a rough example of wrapping `IronOxide` in an `Arc` and sharing it between some threads
```rust
    let sdk: IronOxide = Arc::new(init_sdk());
    let doc = [43u8; 64];

    let mut threads = vec![];
    for _i in 0..10 {
        let sdk_ref = sdk.clone();
        threads.push(std::thread::spawn(move || {
            let _result = sdk_ref.document_encrypt(&doc, &Default::default()).unwrap();
        }));
    }

    let mut joined_count = 0;
    for t in threads {
        t.join().expect("couldn't join");
        joined_count += 1;
    }
    assert_eq!(joined_count, 10)
```

## Changelog
* IronOxide no longer has mutable references in it's API, making it possible to share an IronOxide between threads.
* The RNG used for for AES now periodically reseeds itself.
